verbose_text: Biochemical tests showed hypocalcemia (1.92 mmol/L; normal range, 2.10-2.70 mmol/L), hypophosphatemia (0.17 mmol/L; normal range, 0.81-1.45 mmol/L), an elevated intact parathyroid hormone level (15.26 pmol/L; normal range, 1.60-6.90 pmol/L), and a normal 25-hydroxy vitamin D (100.1 nmol/L; normal range, 47.7-144 nmol/L) and 1,25 (OH) 2 D level (46.82 pmol/L; normal range, 39-193 pmol/L).
